    question: "How long does it take furniture to dry after cleaning?",
    answer: "Drying time depends on the fabric type, cleaning method, and room ventilation. On average, most upholstery dries within 4 to 8 hours.\n\n• Light fabrics and low-moisture methods typically dry faster (around 2–4 hours).\n• Thicker fabrics or deep cleaning may take longer (6–8 hours).\n\nTo speed up drying, we recommend turning on ceiling fans, opening windows, or using your home’s HVAC system to improve airflow. Our technicians will give you specific guidance before leaving so you know exactly what to expect."
  },
